text.section:
A general rescue squad may engage in a specialized rescue squad activity if:
That activity is specified in its mission statement;
The rescue squad has twelve (12) persons including a commanding officer from within its membership of the rescue squad whose mission statement is to engage in the specialized rescue squad activity;
The persons assigned to the specialized rescue squad activity meet the training requirements specified by statute and by administrative regulation;
The rescue squad has the equipment required by administrative regulation to engage in the specialized rescue squad activity listed in its mission statement; and
The rescue squad has a vehicle for transporting the required equipment to the scene.
